The Vice President of the United States, Joe Biden, had a phone call with King Hamad bin Isa al-Khalifa of Bahrain. They discussed the long-standing partnership between the two countries and America's commitment to Bahrain's security, stability, and reform. They also talked about the situation in Iraq and agreed on the importance of Iraqi leaders coming together to address the security threat posed by the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant. Additionally, they discussed ongoing efforts at reform and dialogue within Bahrain, with the Vice President encouraging the government and opposition parties to reach agreement on meaningful reforms that address the aspirations of all Bahrainis.